name: Fraxia_HD_349700
description:
Fraxia_HD takes a random seed and renders a very high resolution 2D map of a time-based function, using controlled noise within a HSB color model. Seed values are observed, but mostly discarded; there seems to be a small zone of viable results; when found, 30 frames rendered at 2048 x 2048. Piece name is the random seed. Although Fraxia_HD shares code with Fraxia, seed values produce differing results.
Seed parameters:
Color change choice is 4; speed is 7.756797
Parameter choice is 4; render choice is 1.
Stripe choice is 0 at 245.0, 306.0
Stripe alternate is 0 at 68.0, 195.0
